{"abstract": "In \u201cExposure,\u201d a new book, the former chief of Olympus of Japan tells how he became a whistle-blower after finding that the company was making questionable, money-losing acquisitions.", "web_url": "https://www.nytimes.com/2012/12/02/business/exposure-the-story-of-a-british-whistle-blower-in-japan.html", "snippet": "In \u201cExposure,\u201d a new book, the former chief of Olympus of Japan tells how he became a whistle-blower after finding that the company was making questionable, money-losing acquisitions.", "lead_paragraph": "THE 2011 financial scandal at the Olympus Corporation, the big Japanese maker of optical equipment, was a head-shaking spectacle. It was rare enough that a Tokyo-based company had elevated Michael Woodford, a Westerner who spoke no Japanese, to its presidency. But when Mr. Woodford discovered loss-hiding shenanigans and turned whistle-blower, he set off a tumult unlike anything that the cosseted world of Japanese business had quite seen. ", "print_section": "BU", "print_page": "5", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2012/12/02/business/02-SHELF/02-SHELF-jumbo.jpg", "height": 1024, "width": 683, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2012/12/02/business/02-SHELF/02-SHELF-superJumbo.jpg", "height": 2048, "width": 1366, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2012/12/02/business/02-SHELF/02-SHELF-thumbStandard.jpg", "height": 75, "width": 75, "subType": "thumbnail", "crop_name": "thumbStandard", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2012/12/02/business/02-SHELF/02-SHELF-thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": 75, "thumbnailheight": 75}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbLarge", "captio